### What this supports

| Placeholder | Example | Behaviour |
|---|---|---|
| Simple variable | `{{name}}` | Looks up `data.name` |
| Dot-notation path | `{{user.address.city}}` | Traverses nested objects safely |
| Nullish fallback | `{{role ?? "guest"}}` | Uses the fallback when the value is `null`/`undefined` |

### Why no `eval()`

`eval()` would allow an attacker who controls the template or data to execute arbitrary code on your server (CWE-94). The implementation above achieves the same flexibility for the common cases (nested paths, fallbacks) through explicit, safe string parsing and object traversal.

